---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
	title="FAQ"
	description="Frequently asked questions about GetCookie community recognition bot."
>
	<h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
	<p class="lead">
		Common questions and answers about GetCookie
	</p>

	<div class="faq-item">
		<p class="faq-question">What is GetCookie?</p>
		<p class="faq-answer">
			GetCookie is a community recognition bot for Discord. Members reward each other by reacting with emojis, giving cookies,
			and climbing leaderboards, and build a culture of appreciation in your community or organization.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="faq-item">
		<p class="faq-question">Can members use other emoji reactions?</p>
		<p class="faq-answer">
			Yes! Any emoji or reaction to messages counts towards the leaderboard. You can customize which emojis are tracked
			and how they contribute to recognition — it's fully customizable to fit your community and organization.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="faq-item">
		<p class="faq-question">How do I give Cookies?</p>
		<p class="faq-answer">
			Simply react with a cookie emoji to someone's message. It's a playful way to show appreciation
			that takes just a second and happens naturally in conversation.
		</p>
	</div>
	
	<div class="faq-item">
		<p class="faq-question">Is GetCookie free?</p>
		<p class="faq-answer">
			GetCookie is free for 14 days. After that, we offer affordable plans for communities of all sizes — including analytics dashboards and engagement insights to help understand your community better.
			Larger organizations can contact us for enterprise pricing.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="faq-item">
		<p class="faq-question">Can I redeem Cookies?</p>
		<p class="faq-answer">
			Yes! Cookies are real crypto tokens. You can redeem them for rewards, transfer them, or hold them before they expire.
			Your Cookies, your choice.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="faq-item">
		<p class="faq-question">Why Discord?</p>
		<p class="faq-answer">
			Discord is where communities thrive. By integrating recognition into Discord, appreciation happens naturally
			without requiring another app or context switch. Just celebrate contributions where you already hang out.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="callout">
		<p>
			<strong>💡 Have a question not listed here?</strong> Reach out to us on
			<a href="https://x.com/GetCookieHQ" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">X (@GetCookieHQ)</a>
			and we'll be happy to help!
		</p>
	</div>
</DocsLayout>
